tles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Pierre d'Auberchicourt was born in 1150, his father, Gauthier II d'Auberchicourt, was 35 and his mother, Adèle de Douai, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Julienne Alexandrine de Valenciennes. He died in 1225, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1150–1225":"1150–1225","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","–1218":"–1218","1115–1165":"1115–1165","1120–1165":"1120–1165","1225":"1225","1115":"1115","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1218":"1218"},"fi":{"1150–1225":"1150–1225","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","–1218":"–1218","1115–1165":"1115–1165","1120–1165":"1120–1165","1225":"1225","1115":"1115","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1218":"1218"},"fr":{"1150–1225":"1150–1225","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","–1218":"–1218","1115–1165":"1115–1165","1120–1165":"1120–1165","1225":"1225","1115":"1115","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1218":"1218","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Pierre d'Auberchicourt est né en 1150, son père, Gauthier II d'Auberchicourt, avait 35 ans et sa mère, Adèle de Douai, avait 30 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Julienne Alexandrine de Valenciennes. Il est décédé en 1225, à l’âge de 75 ans."},"de":{"1150–1225":"1150–1225","1160–Female":"1160–Verstorben","–1218":"–1218","1115–1165":"1115–1165","1120–1165":"1120–1165","1225":"122